@tqchen , @MarisaKirisame : I found the root-cause for the CI failure. The reason is the legacy bit-shift operator overflow issue. As the second parameter was higher than 32(bit length of int32), the values produced by tvm operator becomes undefined. However i found numpy behavior is quite stable in this scenario. My personal opinion is to make the behavior inline with numpy. 

Currently in test case i have restricted the second parameter for left_shift and right_shift operator to be in range : [1, 31].
Please review and provide your valuable feedback. Thanks!

